The key fix is changing from 2 blocks to **1 block**. The single block `hex (0 1 2 3 8 9 10 11)` covers the entire domain, and the `cylinder` boundary patch defines the cylinder surface as the front face `(3 4 11 10)` and the top-front face `(4 7 10 11)`. The `frontAndBack` patch handles the side faces, and `inlet`, `outlet`, `top`, and `bottom` handle the remaining boundaries.

This approach avoids the topology issues entirely because there is only one block, so all boundary faces belong to that single block. The vertex ordering in the single block is straightforward and will not produce inward-pointing faces.

